title: For Sale:  NEW AR 15 with some extras, NEW
location: South West LR, Little Rock, Arkansas
postcontent: Hi Guys, I WILL TAKE THIS ADD DOWN WHEN IT SELLS!!! Today  I have a NEW AR 15, 223 and 5.56 that I built, so here goes the discription as best I can. And my rifle building skills are far superior to my camers skills, lol. It is an OMNI hybrid lower, reinforced polymer with Zinc inserts in all the right places and is rated far beyond the mil spec aluminum lowers for durability and strength, it has a sling mount built right into the end plate for a quick click attachment of a single point or other slings with clasp type clips. I put extended swivel and take down pins for easier break down, I put a trigger and hammer pin locking systen to stop the pins from walking which can be very common with AR's. It has a mil spec Carpenter 258 steel M16 AR 15 full auto BCG, and I also added an enhanced firing pin and extra strength hammer spring for reliability for use with steel cased ammo because of the harder primers on most and I have done this before with great results. I added an extended arm charging handle for easier working for those with arthritis or weaker hands. It has a standard A2 pistol grip but I filed off the finger bump that I find annoying and far from comfortable and includes a brand new 30 round HEXMAG. Now to the upper, It is a HARDENED ARMS Upper that has an A2 profile barrel, 10" quad rail hand guard for easy attachents of the accessories of your choice and a simple but effective tube style red dot sight, the upper is a railed flat top out to the end of the handguard and I have put some camo rail covers on it which you can leave or easily take off. I can tell you the upper and lower are a nice and tight fit, not sloppy like some which means they will stay that way for a long time. Now, other than the uppers maker putting a couple rounds through it for testing it, I have not put a round one through it , I did bore sight it so it should be close enough now for any close encounters and should only require a few clicks at the desired range to finish up sighting it in. I am asking $575 FIRM because of the extras I put into it and is worth every bit of that, I have around $700 into the build so my loss is your gain. This is a fine rifle with nice functional tounches, additions and features and I am sure it will serve you well. PLEASE, NO OUT OF STATE BUYERS, NO CHECKS, IN PERSON AND CASH ONLY!!!! I AM ONLY SELLING IT BECAUSE I want a different rifle and am now retired and disabled living on a very small fixed income so to have what I want I have to part with something that I built for myself.
